1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:06,690
Our combined carpentry talent equaled zero, and the end product clearly reflected that fact.

2
00:00:07,200 --> 00:00:12,130
Shortly afterward a good friend stopped by, and upon seeing what we had done,

3
00:00:12,241 --> 00:00:15,891
asked, What's that you've stuck up there among the trees?

4
00:00:16,000 --> 00:00:18,130
That's not a doghouse, is it?

5
00:00:18,400 --> 00:00:20,211
I replied that it was.

6
00:00:20,560 --> 00:00:24,851
Then he pointed out just a few of our mistakes and summed it all up with,

7
00:00:24,960 --> 00:00:26,851
Why didn't you get a plan?

8
00:00:27,041 --> 00:00:30,851
Nobody these days builds a doghouse without a blueprint.

9
00:00:31,601 --> 00:00:37,491
And please, as you visualize your future, don't be afraid to be blue sky.

10
00:00:37,520 --> 00:00:41,250
People these days are measured by the size of their dreams.

11
00:00:41,520 --> 00:00:45,010
No one accomplishes more than he sets out to accomplish.

12
00:00:45,120 --> 00:00:47,810
So, visualize a big future.

13
00:00:48,801 --> 00:00:54,051
Here is a word-for-word excerpt from the life plan of one of my former trainees.

14
00:00:54,241 --> 00:00:55,251
Listen to it.

15
00:00:55,521 --> 00:00:59,330
Note how well this fellow visualized his home future.

16
00:00:59,601 --> 00:01:04,371
As he wrote this, it is obvious he really saw himself in the future.

17
00:01:05,041 --> 00:01:08,291
My home goal is to own a country estate.

18
00:01:08,561 --> 00:01:14,371
The house will be of the typical southern manor type, two stories, white columns and all.

19
00:01:14,721 --> 00:01:20,131
We will have the grounds fenced in, and probably will have a fish pond or two on the place,

20
00:01:20,161 --> 00:01:22,771
as my wife and I both enjoy fishing.

21
00:01:23,121 --> 00:01:26,690
We will keep our Doberman kennels back of the house somewhere.

22
00:01:26,881 --> 00:01:32,611
The thing I have always wanted is a long winding driveway with trees lining each side.

23
00:01:33,121 --> 00:01:36,291
But a house is not necessarily a home.

24
00:01:36,561 --> 00:01:42,291
I am going to do everything I can to make our house more than just a place to eat and sleep.

25
00:01:42,801 --> 00:01:46,531
Of course we do not intend to leave God out of our plans,

26
00:01:46,561 --> 00:01:51,570
and throughout the years we will spend a certain amount of time in church activities.

27
00:01:52,321 --> 00:01:57,731
Ten years from now, I want to be in a position to take a family cruise around the world.

28
00:01:58,001 --> 00:02:03,731
I would like very much to do this before the family gets scattered all over the world by marriages,

29
00:02:03,731 --> 00:02:08,291
etc. If we can't find the time to make the cruise all at once,

30
00:02:08,401 --> 00:02:14,611
we will put it into four or five separate vacations and visit a different part of the world each year.

31
00:02:15,041 --> 00:02:21,491
Naturally, all these plans in Home Department depend on how well things go in my Work Department,

32
00:02:21,601 --> 00:02:25,651
so I'll have to keep on the ball if I'm to accomplish all this.

33
00:02:26,641 --> 00:02:29,411
This plan was written five years ago.

34
00:02:29,601 --> 00:02:32,931
The trainee then owned two small dime stores.

35
00:02:33,201 --> 00:02:33,730
Now he owns five, and he has purchased seventeen acres for his country estate.
